The paper deals with Internet topology discovery and specifically focuses on revealing MPLS tunnels, which are a crucial aspect of network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the limitations of traceroute and proposes an extension to it, which involves detecting patterns in traceroute output, indicating the presence of hidden tunnels. This aspect of the paper makes it relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The paper also involves tuning parameters and conducting a measurement campaign, which falls under the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper also discusses the deployment of the proposed method on a platform, which is relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. Finally, the paper deals with Internet topology, which is a topic that falls under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category.
